#compdef filescope-nexus filescope-helper filescope-install
# ============================================================================
# filescope-{nexus,helper,install} - codebase dependency-graph MCP server
#                                     for AI coding agents (Node, MIT)
#
# Author : admica
# Upstream: https://github.com/admica/FileScopeMCP
# npm    : FileScopeMCP
#
# FileScopeMCP analyzes a codebase, builds a per-file
# dependency graph, runs community detection (Louvain) on the
# graph to identify modules / subsystems, and surfaces the
# resulting "importance score" + per-file context to AI
# coding agents (Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode, etc.) via the
# Model Context Protocol. Three bundled binaries:
#
#   filescope-nexus   - HTTP server hosting the FileScope UI +
#                       JSON API for multi-repo browsing
#   filescope-helper  - Claude Code hook helper (PreToolUse +
#                       SessionStart hooks); invoked by your
#                       Claude Code hook config; reads payload
#                       from stdin + emits hook response on
#                       stdout per the hook protocol
#   filescope-install - opinionated installer that registers
#                       FileScopeMCP with Claude Code + writes
#                       the CLAUDE.md primer + prints the hook
#                       config snippet for the user to paste
#
# Architecture:
#   - tree-sitter parses each source file
#   - per-language symbol extractor (Go, TypeScript, Rust,
#     Python, Java, C, ...) emits import/call edges
#   - graphology assembles the typed graph of file->file edges
#   - graphology-communities-louvain runs Louvain community
#     detection to find modules
#   - PageRank / centrality measures produce the per-file
#     importance score
#   - SQLite (.filescope/data.db) persists the index + graph
#
# Flag summaries:
#
#   filescope-nexus:
#     --port <port>         - HTTP port (default 1234)
#     --host <addr>         - bind address (default 0.0.0.0)
#
#   filescope-helper <subcommand>:
#     pre-tool-use          - Claude Code PreToolUse hook
#     session-start         - Claude Code SessionStart hook
#     (reads JSON hook payload from stdin)
#
#   filescope-install:
#     --claude-code         - target Claude Code (default)
#     --hermes              - target Hermes (Phase 4; reserved)
#     -y, --yes             - non-interactive mode
#     --no-hooks            - skip printing the hook config snippet
#
# Environment for filescope-helper:
#   FILESCOPE_HOOKS=off     - disable all hook output without
#                             removing the user's hook config
#
# The graphology lane is built on `graphology ^0.26.0` +
# `graphology-communities-louvain ^2.0.2` + `graphology-types
# ^0.24.8` (declared verbatim at upstream package.json HEAD),
# the canonical Node typed-graph library by Guillaume Plique
# (jacomyal) - github.com/graphology/graphology, 1900+ stars.
# graphology is the JavaScript equivalent of petgraph (Rust)
# + gonum/graph (Go): a typed graph data structure with a
# growing companion ecosystem of algorithm packages
# (graphology-shortest-path, graphology-communities-louvain,
# graphology-pagerank, graphology-traversal, graphology-
# layout-forceatlas2, etc.). The library's design is closely
# aligned with the gephi-ecosystem network-analysis stack -
# Guillaume Plique works at the Sciences Po Médialab, which
# pioneered the gephi.org graph-visualization tool.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 230 :: Graph data structures + algorithms (typed graphs + traversal)
# Round 1390 :: TS-Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 230 (223rd axis closed)
# Round-number landmark: Axis 230 closes at triple-285 (Rust/Go/Node all =285)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : petgraph/petgraph            [R1388 _cxx2flow]
#   Go      : gonum/gonum (graph subpkg)   [R1389 _sbotcli]
#   TS/Node : jacomyal/graphology          [R1390 THIS FILE]
#
# graphology rounds out the Axis 230 trio with the
# *visualization-adjacent* end of the spectrum. petgraph
# (Rust) emphasizes correctness + zero-allocation traversal
# for embedded use cases like cxx2flow's CFG; gonum/graph
# (Go) bundles graph algorithms inside a broader scientific-
# computing library for use in social-graph queries like
# sbotcli; graphology (Node) is the only one of the three
# with a first-class gephi-style network-visualization
# companion ecosystem.
#
# The cross-language structural pattern across Axis 230:
# graph libraries are *interface-bound*, not *spec-bound*.
# Unlike axes where an RFC pins the wire format (DNS, MQTT,
# TLS) or a paper pins the algorithm output (fzf-v2, LZ4,
# XXH64), graph libraries can each pick their own
# representation - adjacency lists vs adjacency matrices,
# typed-node-id vs string-id, mutable vs persistent. The
# user-visible *operations* (BFS, DFS, dijkstra, PageRank)
# are interchangeable across libraries but the underlying
# Graph<N, E> types are not interoperable - exporting from
# petgraph to graphology requires serializing to DOT or
# JSON-graph as an intermediate format.
#
# Axis 230 closes the round 1390 cycle - 223rd axis closed
# total, at the round-number landmark of Axis 230.
# ============================================================================

_filescope-nexus() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    case "$service" in
        filescope-nexus)
            _arguments -s -S \
                '--port[HTTP port (default 1234)]:port:' \
                '--host[bind address (default 0.0.0.0)]:host:' \
                '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
            ;;
        filescope-helper)
            _arguments -s -S \
                '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
                '1:subcommand:(pre-tool-use session-start)'
            ;;
        filescope-install)
            _arguments -s -S \
                '--claude-code[target Claude Code (default)]' \
                '--hermes[target Hermes (Phase 4; reserved)]' \
                '(-y --yes)'{-y,--yes}'[non-interactive mode]' \
                '--no-hooks[skip printing the hook config snippet]' \
                '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
            ;;
    esac
}

_filescope-nexus "$@"
